## ­¤Üó Deployment

### Environment Variables

Before deploying, ensure you have a `.env` file with all required environment variables:

```bash
# Copy the example file
cp .env.example .env

# Edit with your production values
nano .env
```

### Health Checks

The application includes:
- Graceful shutdown handling (SIGTERM/SIGINT)
- Environment validation on startup

### Common Deployment Platforms

#### Fly.io

```bash
# Install flyctl
curl -L https://fly.io/install.sh | sh

# Launch your app
fly launch

# Deploy
fly deploy
```

#### Railway

```bash
# Install Railway CLI
npm i -g @railway/cli

# Login and init
railway login
railway init

# Deploy
railway up
```

#### Render

1. Connect your repository at render.com
2. Select "Node" as the environment
3. Set build command: `bun install && bun run build`
4. Set start command: `bun start`

#### DigitalOcean App Platform

1. Connect your repository
2. Configure build command: `bun install && bun run build`
3. Configure run command: `bun start`
4. Set environment variables
5. Deploy

